                            </msItem>
                            
                            <msItem xml:id="Wellcome_Malay_1_Part_1_Item_2">
                                                              
                                <note><locus>PP. 13-28</locus>: Laws</note>
                                
                                <note><p>The text of laws is a description of the (matrilineal) Minangkabau systemm originally from <settlement>Sumatra</settlement>. 
                                    The text is a short paraphrase of the main institutions of Minangkabau legal thought.</p>
                                    <p>The language is Malay rather than Minangkabau, though dialect words from the latter do occur.</p> 
                                </note>
                            
                                <filiation>The text is a paraphrase of <ref>Maxwell 118a in the Royal Asiatic Society</ref> See <ref>R. O. Windstedt and P.E. de Josselin de Jong. 'A Digest of Customary Law from Sungei Ujong, JMBRAS. 3(1954), 1-71)</ref>.</filiation>
                                
                                <incipit><locus>P. 13</locus>
                                    <note>The text begins with an invocation to Allah, the writer's name (<persName>Tuan Guru Haji Abdul Kahar</persName>) and a brief explanation of the matrilineal adat system.</note>
                                </incipit>
                                                           
                            </msItem>
                            
